<li id="cite_note-ShulmanSandberg2010-53"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Technological_singularity#cite_ref-ShulmanSandberg2010_53-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFShulmanAnders_Sandberg2010" class="citation journal">Shulman, Carl; Anders Sandberg (2010).  Mainzer, Klaus (ed.). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://intelligence.org/files/SoftwareLimited.pdf">"Implications of a Software-Limited Singularity"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>ECAP10: VIII European Conference on Computing and Philosophy</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">17 May</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=ECAP10%3A+VIII+European+Conference+on+Computing+and+Philosophy&amp;rft.atitle=Implications+of+a+Software-Limited+Singularity&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.aulast=Shulman&amp;rft.aufirst=Carl&amp;rft.au=Anders+Sandberg&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fintelligence.org%2Ffiles%2FSoftwareLimited.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATechnological+singularity" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
